total_energy_consumption,scope_2_emissions_tco2e,2,forbid_reverse,2,"Scope 2 emissions are indirectly generated by the purchased electricity, heat, cooling, or steam that the company consumes. Luo and Tang (2014) examined the relationship between carbon emissions and shareholder wealth, showing that, unlike Scope 1, Scope 2 emissions are not negatively correlated with abnormal returns. Choi et al. (2021) produced evidence that the negative association between carbon emissions and firm value only applies to Scope 1 emissions because those are the ones that investors use to estimate a company's potential liabilities.",735c8d3e-d9bf-46cc-9420-0cc62447afb7; cd2205e2-02b5-49b1-a547-3e9f6f80295a,yes,auto-approved: tier 2 structural/temporal/impossibility
customer_satisfaction_score,turnover_rate,2,forbid_reverse,1,CS has a strong association with retention (r = 0.60) and WOM (r = 0.68) and is moderately correlated with spending (r = 0.28) and price outcomes (r = 0.39),customer_satisfaction_meta_analysis,yes,auto-approved: tier 2 structural/temporal/impossibility
diversity_representation,net_profit_margin,2,forbid_reverse,1,the presence of women in senior management is consistently associated with high performance in most sectors,gender_diversity_ibex35_financial_performance,yes,auto-approved: tier 2 structural/temporal/impossibility
